President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Georgia due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes that occurred on January 12, 2023. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Assistance will be available to affected individuals for temporary housing, home repairs, and low-cost loans for uninsured property losses. Federal funding will also be available for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures. John F. Boyle has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Damage assessments are ongoing, and more counties and forms of assistance may be designated later. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance through the FEMA website, phone, or app. For further information, the FEMA News Desk can be contacted.